race.comment: Does look a race in two between the Tesio Stakes quinella. SHE'S A HUSTLER (5) won that race with a strong performance, sitting on speed and kicking clear to win well. She was well weighted there and is up to 57kg now but she's a mare with plenty of upside and she can improve again. SEA WHAT I SEE (6) tried hard behind SHE'S A HUSTLER there and now meets her 6kg better off at the weights for a 1.3 length defeat. She's got a great record herself and looks the clear danger again. Wary of ALALCANCE (1) who resumes. She only had one run last time in and was well beaten with 61kg in a Wyong Cup having looked very progressive in the Autumn. The late market will be key to her chances. BLINDEDBYTHELIGHT (12) was good in the Tesio when making ground for fifth. She's on the up and should run well. MOVIN OUT (10) needs to find her best, if they run along in front it'll help her settle.
